). Very similar to ♀ , but smaller and more slender (body length 59.0–64.0 mm). Transverse black bands on abdominal sternites II to poculum. Vomer small and triangular with an up-curving hook with acute apex. Poculum flat with the posterior margin rounded, posteromedially slightly incised, at best reaching centre of anal segment.
